# Description

This PR brings a number of improvements to the Teams System in the backend. The detailed changes are listed below commit-wise -

*Commit 1*
- Created various access decorators which can be used on routes to restrict who can access it.
- E.g. Route with @project_owner_only can only be accessed by the creator of a project

*Commit 2*
- Added access decorators on appropriate routes
- Removed redundant code on those routes

*Commit 3*
- Created a route for a member to leave a project
- Added message for this route in the logs decorator

*Commit 4*
- Created routes for granting and revoking admin access to users in a project
- Added messages for both routes in the logs decorator

*Commit 5*
- Resolved merge conflicts

*Commit 6 & 7*
- Modified get team by id route to also fetch last 5 logs and details of team members for showing in the TeamDetailsScreen in mobile application

*Commit 8*
- Created a route to get the roles the current user has in a project 
- This route will help in restricting access in the Mobile Application, regulating which actions the user can perform based on their roles

Fixes #592 

## Type of change

- [ ] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)
- [x] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)
- [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that would cause existing functionality to not work as expected)
- [ ] This change requires a documentation update

# How Has This Been Tested?

Demo Video has been provided below

**Test Configuration**:

- Postman
- Windows 10

*Granting and revoking admin access*

![make-remove-admin](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/122252588-19c56200-cee9-11eb-80ea-bf123bf4578d.gif)

*Leaving a project*

![leave-project](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/122252617-2053d980-cee9-11eb-9755-9fd0e3ec8a7c.gif)

# Description

This PR includes the frontend implementation for improving team management. The detailed changes are provided below commit-wise.

**Commit 1**
- Created Team Details Page which can be visited by clicking on a Team in the Project Details Page

![team details](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/126672915-8230b3ac-bb45-4619-aab0-db47436bfa06.png)

**Commit 2**
- Implemented the functionality to delete a team

![delete team](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/126672964-7f8b0f63-7ee5-4498-864b-526c45d8707d.gif)

**Commit 3**
- Implemented the functionality to update a team

![edit team](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/126673095-76e6948b-452b-4523-aeaa-c5908511efb0.gif)

**Commit 4**
- Implemented the functionality to add a team member

![add member](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/126673118-2386ef2b-6680-4957-8558-8da86bf11032.gif)

**Commit 5**
- Implemented the functionality to remove a team member

![remove member](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/126673146-0d4de033-774e-4e9f-b4ea-4a1f38e5e583.gif)

**Commit 6**
- Add minor UI changes in Team Details Page

**Commit 7**
- Implemented the functionality to leave a project

![leave project](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/126673176-64bf8f77-d346-4ef9-90d8-943c1c90e5bf.gif)

**Commit 8**
- Implemented role-based access control so that specific actions within a project can only be done by members with suitable role
- E.g models can be added/deleted/edited by members who have 'admin' or 'models' role

![role control](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45410599/126673203-32373d68-4b03-423a-a86e-0cbfccfcf467.png)

# Description

This Pull Request contains the backend implementation of the Project Activity Tracking System. The detailed changes are provided below commit-wise.

*Commit 1*
- Created the db model for a Log

*Commit 2*
- Created the log decorator
- Created a log helpers file

*Commit 3*
- Added the logs decorator on route whose activity needs to be tracked
- Areas covered - projects, teams, images, labels, mlclassifiers

*Commit 4*
- Created the logs controller to fetch the logs project-wise, category-wise, user-wise, entity-wise
- Created additional helper functions

*Commit 5*
- Modified fetch project by id route to also show the last 5 logs of a project
- These logs can then be shown as recent activity in project details screen

*Commit 6*
- Added username field to Log model

Fixes #593

# Description

This PR implements the Project Activity Tracking System in the Mobile Application, using the backend features implemented in #604 . The detailed changes are listed below commit-wise:

*Commit 1*
- Created Log model
- Added recent activtity logs list to Project model

*Commit 2*
- Created recent activity section in ProjectDetailsScreen which shows last 5 logs of the project
- Added a 'More' button option which goes to an empty ProjectActivityScreen when clicked
- Created routing for the ActivityLogsScreen

*Commit 3*
- Created route for fetching all activity logs of a project
- Created a ProjectActivityBloc and ProjectActivityState for state management
- Implemented the functionality to view all activity logs in ProjectActivityScreen

*Commit 4*
- Added a loading indicator in ProjectActivityScreen
- Implemented color coding in logs in ProjectActivityScreen

*Commit 5*
- Created UI for the filters bottom sheet
- Created a reusable dropdown widget

*Commit 6*
- Used ProjectDetailBloc in the bottom sheet to get names of all project members for member-specific filtering
- Replaced text field for member name with dropdown for better experience

*Commit 7*
- Implemented routes for fetching category-specific and member-specific logs
- Completed the filtering functionality in ProjectActivityScreen

*Commit 8*
- Ran into a small issue during development. That in the logs controller in API, we were fetching member specific logs using user_id. But in the ProjectDetailBloc, we only had email of members.
- So, I modified the API route to fetch member logs using email

*Commit 9*
- Implemented the functionality to view logs specific to a particular entity (image, model, label etc).
- Implemented the route to fetch entity specific logs
- Created a new to route to view ProjectActivityScreen only for entities
- Added functionality to view these logs for models, images and labels.

*Commit 10*
- Added a empty placeholder in ProjectActivityScreen to show when there are no logs.

Fixes #593 

## Type of change

- [ ] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)
- [x] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)
- [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that would cause existing functionality to not work as expected)

pr_title: Migrate to Flutter 2.0 and fix Dependency Versions
pr_body: # Description This PR involves migrating the Mobile Application to Flutter 2.0, while fixing dependency versions and bringing Null Safety support. The detailed changes are provided below, commit-wise: *Commit 1* - Upgraded all packages to their null safe versions, if available. - Fixed errors caused due to the upgrades. *Commit 2* - Migrated the application to Null Safety using the Migration Tool *Commit 3* - Removed unused imports *Commit 4* - Removed deprecation warnings caused due to the migration *Commit 5* - Due to changes in button styling, the color of buttons had changed to default blue - Fixed it by defining a TextButton theme *Commit 6* - The provider package has undergone some changes and now, when we are only using it trigger an action (e.g. button click) , we have explicity write ```listen: false``` - Made that change throughout the application wherever necessary *Commit 7* - ```page_view_indicator``` package being used by the app doesn't support Null Safety yet. - Replaced it with another compatible package. - Changes can be viewed in the GIF provided below. *Commit 8* - ```charts_flutter``` package also doesn't support Null Safety yet. - Commented out the parts where it was being used, as it's only being used in a dummy class *Commit 9* - Some provider calls related to the issue in Commit 6 were still remaining, fixed those. - Fixed a remaining issue in the TextFormField to support Null Safety Fixes #596 ## Type of change - [x] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue) - [x] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality) - [ ] Breaking change (fix or feature that would cause existing functionality to not work as expected) - [ ] This change requires a documentation update # How Has This Been Tested? Used and explored the app extensively to make sure that no existing functionality has been broken. **Test Configuration**: - Realme 3 Pro - Android 10 # Checklist: - [x] My code follows the style guidelines of this project - [x] I have performed a self-review of my own code - [ ] I have commented my code, particularly in hard-to-understand areas - [ ] I have made corresponding changes to the documentation - [x] My changes generate no new warnings - [ ] I have added tests that prove my fix is effective or that my feature works - [x] New and existing unit tests pass locally with my changes - [x] Any dependent changes have been merged and published in downstream modules

pr_title: Implemented Backend Service Selection functionality in Mobile Application
pr_body:
# Description

This PR includes the implementation of Backend Service Selection functionality in the Mobile Application. The detailed changes are provided below commit-wise:

*Commit 1*
- Created the UI for backend selection screen
- Created the route for backend selection screen
- Also add option in profile screen to access the backend selection screen

*Commit 2*
- Created init screen, which will now be the home screen of the application
- Every time the app start, the init screen will check if there is a url present in the local storage
- If yes, load main screen like before
- If no, load backend selection screen

*Commit 3*
- Implemented the functionality to save url to local storage

*Commit 4*
- Implemented the functionality to edit the url stored in local storage

*Commit 5*
- Created a Dio interceptor which will intercept each request, fetch base url from local storage, and then set that url as base url for each request.
- Deleted ```config_example.dart``` file which was earlier used for storing base url

Fixes #597
